# Dataset stats ‚Äî showcasing the post-v1.21 API

A small "weather log analytics" pipeline using
`union` / `zipWithIndex` / `top` / `min` / `max` / `sum` / `avg` /
`countByValue`. Runs on all three backends.

```scalascript
// Two days of recorded temperatures (¬∞C)
val day1 = Dataset.of(8, 12, 15, 14, 11, 9, 7)
val day2 = Dataset.of(10, 13, 17, 18, 16, 12, 10)

// Combined sample
val all = day1.union(day2)

println(s"samples: ${all.count()}")
println(s"min: ${all.min()}, max: ${all.max()}")
println(s"sum: ${all.sum()}, avg: ${all.avg()}")

// Top-3 hottest readings across both days
println(s"top-3: ${all.top(3).mkString(", ")}")

// Index each reading from day1 so you can tell where extremes happened
day1.zipWithIndex.collect().foreach { case (t, h) => println(s"hour $h: $t¬∞C") }

// Count readings ‚â• 15¬∞C ("hot") via countByValue + map
println("---hot vs cool---")
val labels = all.map(t => if t >= 15 then "hot" else "cool").countByValue()
List("cool", "hot").foreach(k => println(s"$k: ${labels(k)}"))
```
